    "title": "Prayer of Parents for a Son or Daughter in the Armed Forces, by Rabbi Max Klein (1951)",
    "author": "Aharon N. Varady (transcription)",
    "coauthors": [
        {
            "name": "Max D. Klein",
            "bio": "Rabbi Max Klein was born in New York City in 1885 and was ordained by the Jewish Theological Seminary in 1911. Soon afterward, he began serving as rabbi for Congregation Adath Jeshurun in Philadelphia. Formerly a Reform synagogue, under Rabbi Klein's leadership it became one of the initial congregations affiliated with the United Synagogue of America (now called the United Synagogue for Conservative Judaism). In addition to serving as rabbi at Adath Jeshurun in Philadelphia until 1960, Rabbi Klein wrote, edited, and translated two prayer books: <em>Seder Avodah for Sabbath, Festivals, and Weekdays</em> (1951) and <em>Seder Avodah for Rosh Hashanah and Yom Kippur</em> (1960). He died in 1973.",
            "website": "",
            "avatar": "https://opensiddur.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/max-klein-96x96.jpg",
